Fifteen earthquakes struck in either Asia or Africa between January
1998 and June 1990.  Four of those were considered major because they
registered Richter Scale readings above seven. There were four
earthquakes that caused 1,000 or more deaths, and only two of those
had readings above seven on the Richter.  </SUM>
